We are going to need the first order partial derivatives of 
$f(x,y)=ye^{-x}$ at $(x,y)=(1,e)$. Here they are.
\begin{align*}
f_x(x,y)&= -ye^{-x} & f_x(1,e)&=-e\,e^{-1}=-1 \\
f_y(x,y)&=e^{-x}    & f_y(1,e)&= e^{-1}
\end{align*}

(a) The linear approximation to $f(x,y)$ at $(x,y)=(1,e)$ is
