(c) We'll start with part (c) and follow the procedure given in 
\S\eref{CLP200}{subsec memory aid} in the CLP-3 text. We are to compute the
derivative of $h(x,y,z)=f\big(u(x,y,z),v(x,y),w(x)\big)$ with respect to 
