\begin{question}
What is wrong with the following argument? Suppose that $w=f(x,y,z)$
and $z=g(x,y)$. By the chain rule,
\begin{align*}
\pdiff{w}{x}
=\pdiff{w}{x}\pdiff{x}{x}
+\pdiff{w}{y}\pdiff{y}{x}
+\pdiff{w}{z}\pdiff{z}{x}
=\pdiff{w}{x}
+\pdiff{w}{z}\pdiff{z}{x}
