(a) Since, in polar coordinates,
\begin{equation*}
\frac{xy}{x^2+y^2}=\frac{r^2\cos\theta\sin\theta}{r^2}
=\cos\theta\sin\theta
\end{equation*}
we have that the limit does not exist. For example, 
\begin{itemize}
\item if we send $(x,y)$
