So
\begin{equation*}
\bar x^2+\bar y^2=(\bar x-a)^2+\bar y^2=(\bar x-b)^2+(\bar y-c)^2 
\end{equation*}
or, subtracting $\bar x^2+\bar y^2$ from the three equal expressions,
\begin{equation*}
0=a^2-2a\bar x=b^2-2b\bar x+c^2-2c\bar y
\end{equation*}
which implies
