\end{equation*}
The radius is the distance from the vertex $(0,0)$ to the centre 
$(\bar x,\bar y)$, which is
$\sqrt{\big(\frac{a}{2}\big)^2+\big(\frac{b^2+c^2-ab}{2c}\big)^2}$.

\end{solution}

