\begin{solution}
By definition, $f(x) = x^3$ is differentiable at $x = 0$
if the limit
$$
\lim_{h\rightarrow 0}\frac{f(h)-f(0)}{h}
=\lim_{h\rightarrow 0}\frac{h^3-0}{h}
$$
