solution:
\begin{solution}
Using the chain rule, followed by the product rule:
\begin{align*}
\diff{}{x}\left\{e^{x\cos(x)}\right\}&=e^{\textcolor{red}{x\cos x}}\diff{}{x}\left\{
\textcolor{red}{x\cos x}\right\}
\\&=[\cos x -x\sin x]e^{x\cos(x)}
\end{align*}
\end{solution}

