solution:
\begin{solution}
This requires us to apply the chain rule twice.
\begin{align*}
  \diff{}{x} \left\{ e^{\sin^2(x)} \right\}
  &= e^{\sin^2(x)} \cdot \diff{}{x} \left\{ \sin^2(x)\right\}\\
  &= e^{\sin^2(x)} (2\sin(x)) \cdot \diff{}{x} \sin(x) \\
  &= e^{\sin^2(x)} (2\sin(x)) \cdot \cos(x)
\end{align*}
\end{solution}

