=\dblInt_R\Big[1-6x^2-3y^2\Big]\ \dee{x}\,\dee{y}
\end{equation*}
where $R$ is the region in the $xy$-plane whose boundary is $C$. Observe
that the integrand $1-6x^2-3y^2$ is positive in the elliptical region
