x^2+y^2 = 8-2x\qquad\text{or}\qquad
   (x+1)^2+y^2 =9
\end{equation*}
So the curve $C$ is also the intersection of
\begin{equation*}
(x+1)^2+y^2 =9\qquad\text{and}\qquad  z = 8-2x
\end{equation*}
$(x+1)^2+y^2 =9$ is the circle of radius $3$ centred on $(-1,0)$ and can
